 and resolution reduction. This leads to the conclusion that\nthe flat, albeit complex, landscape for polaron migration in SrI$_2$ is key for\nunderstanding its outstanding performance. This insight provides important\nguidance not only for the future development of high-performance scintillators\nbut also of other materials, for which large polaron mobilities are crucial\nsuch as batteries and solid state ionic conductors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Apr 2016 22:10:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Jun 2016 17:30:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-19"}
